## Mathematical content

- An elementary disjunction is a finite disjunction of literals.
- A maxterm relative to a finite variable list `P_1,\ldots,P_n` is an elementary disjunction containing exactly one of `P_i` or `\neg P_i` for each `i`.
- A formula is in conjunctive normal form if it is a finite conjunction of clauses.
- The existence theorem states: for every `\varphi\in\WFF`, there exists a formula `\psi\in\WFF` in conjunctive normal form such that `\varphi\equiv\psi`.

